[Chikungunya virus is endemic in India. There were scattered outbreaks of chikungunya virus infections in several localities around India last year (2013). A report last year was the 1st one of an outbreak in Tamil Nadu state that has come to ProMED's attention. Now, we have the 2nd outbreak report there. It is not clear whether the diagnoses of chikungunya virus infection is based solely on clinical grounds or whether some or all cases are laboratory diagnosed as well. Cleaning or eliminating water containers is a prudent way to affect vector mosquito control. One hope that the intensive cleanup campaign being launched successfully reduces the numbers of vector mosquitoes and transmission rates.

Maps of India can be seen at http://www.mapsofindia.com/images2/india-map.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2776252,41078. - Mod.TY]
